245  library_note "use has_coe_t"
246  "We use the class `has_coe_t` instead of `has_coe` if the first-argument is a variable.
247  Using `has_coe` would cause looping of type-class inference. See
248  <https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/remove.20all.20instances.20with.20variable.20domain>"
